                            Club Lloyds Terms &amp; Conditions 
                        </div>
                        <div class="collapse__content">
                            <div class="collapse__wrapper">

<div class="container container-tiny generic-content__text written-content">
<ol class="list">
    <li><span style="font-weight: lighter;">If you select cinema as your &ldquo;Lifestyle Benefit&rdquo;, the administrator will use the postcode originally provided to Lloyds Bank to identify your nearest cinema supplier. You will have ability to manually change the allocated cinema supplier within the timeframe stipulated within your welcome or renewal letter or email. Your final choice must be communicated to the administrator no later than the final date outlined in your welcome or renewal letter or email. If no manual selection is made within the specified timeframe, you will be allocated your nearest cinema supplier (for new customers) or be deemed to have chosen the same benefit and supplier as for your previous benefit year (for renewal customers).</span></li>
    <li><span style="font-weight: lighter;"></span><span style="font-weight: lighter;">These vouchers must be used at the time of exchange for any one regularly scheduled film performance, subject to availability.&nbsp;</span></li>
    <li>
    These vouchers may not be combined with any other ticket offer. They may not be used for premieres or special events. </li>
    <li>These vouchers are for personal use, may not be exchanged for use at a later date nor may they be exchanged for cash or merchandise or otherwise transferred to any third party for commercial gain. </li>
    <li>These vouchers are not subject to any time extensions. </li>
    <li>These vouchers may not be re-sold. Each voucher can only be used once and will expire on the earlier of the date of redemption and the date of expiry set out on the voucher. </li>
    <li>Film classification rules apply. ID may be required. </li>
    <li>The Cinema Manager&rsquo;s decision is final. </li>
    <li>The administrator aims to dispatch vouchers within 3 working days by post and 3 working days by email. </li>
    <li>If you wish to purchase 3D glasses at the cinema, there will be an additional charge. </li>
    <li>For any lost or stolen vouchers, please contact the Club Lloyds helpdesk on 0345 3030303 (+441733 462224 if calling from abroad). Any lost or stolen vouchers will only be re-issued twice. </li>
    <li>Each voucher can be exchanged for a Standard 2D admission ticket to any Vue Cinema (excluding Gold Class, VIP and Premiere seating, 3D, Special, Alternative or Event Cinema screening or Over 18&rsquo;s Screenings, Scene Westfield, Xtreme Screens). </li>
    <li>The Standard 2D admission ticket is valid as part payment for 3D, VIP, Xtreme, Scene and Gold. Upgrades to 3D, VIP, Xtreme, Scene, Gold are available on payment of the difference in cost between Standard adult price for the upgraded experience and standard Adult 2D admission. </li>
    <li>These vouchers may be used to book a cinema ticket online at www.myvue.com, or can be exchanged for a 2D admission ticket at the box office of any Vue cinema box office.  These vouchers may not be used to reserve an admission ticket by telephone. </li>
    <li>Club Lloyds vouchers cannot be used for Event Cinema screenings, including: NT Live, ROH Live, RSC, Met Opera, Bolshoi, Theatre, Special Events and Bollywood. </li>
    <li>Please note that due to Vue&rsquo;s advance booking policy the film or performance you wish to attend may be sold out and seats might not be available. The holder is not entitled to any preferential right over other cinema patrons. </li>
    <li>Vue reserves the right to amend these terms and conditions at any time and without notice.  Such changes will be posted on www.myvue.com. Alternatively you can obtain a copy of the latest terms by calling Vue Guest Services on 0345 308 4620 (local rates apply) or by emailing customerservices@vuemail.com.</li>
